## Case Study: ChatGPT Tweets on Creativity

In recent years, the concept of human **creativity** has been progressively redefined in light of new digital technologies and artificial intelligence (AI). Innovative tools like ChatGPT, developed by OpenAI, represent an emerging frontier in human-machine interaction. ChatGPT is an advanced natural language processing (NLP) model capable of autonomously generating text, answering questions, and assisting with various creative tasks. The introduction of this technology has sparked a debate on how AI can influence, support, and even amplify human creativity.

This project aims to analyze **tweets** on Twitter discussing ChatGPT to understand users’ reactions to a crucial question: Can ChatGPT truly enhance human creativity? Through collecting and analyzing these tweets, the objective is to understand **if and how users perceive ChatGPT** as a tool that can enrich creative processes, contributing to idea generation, problem-solving, or content creation in artistic, literary, and professional fields.

The hands-on component of this project is organized into **five assignments**, each focusing on a specific aspect of text analysis applied to the topic of **ChatGPT tweets on creativity**:

